## Common Pitfalls

### Content Key Mismatch
Content items may use `q`/`a` keys in FAQ and privacy sections, not `pregunta`/`respuesta` or `question`/`answer`. Same for glossary using `q`/`a` not `term`/`definition`. Always check the actual JSON structure and support all variants:
```
pregunta || question || q
respuesta || answer || a
term || title || q
definition || description || a
```

### images.json Path Prefix
When migrating from paragu-ai-builder, ALL image paths in images.json use `/sites/nexa-paraguay/images/...` prefix. Batch-replace to `/images/...` for standalone deployment. Check `src`, `fallbackSrc`, `fallback`, and `basePath` fields.

### images.json Must Be in Docker Image
The Dockerfile's runner stage must `COPY --from=builder ... /app/images.json ./images.json` or images won't load at runtime.

### Data Passed Directly vs via pageContent
When `resolveContent(content, 'faqPage.full')` returns the full FAQ object, the component gets it as `pageContent`. The component should NOT look for `pageContent.faq` — the data IS `pageContent`. Support a `data` prop fallback.

### Stats Are Fabricated
By default, content files have fake stats (`+500 Familias reubicadas`, `98% Tasa de éxito`). Replace with real numbers or honest aspirational wording before launch:
```
"+100 Familias asesoradas"
"+5 Años de experiencia"
``` 
Remove the fabricated percentage entirely.
